==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Handkerchief
<hw>Hand"ker*chief</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧⟦nsm⟧"k⟦etil⟧r*ch⟦icr⟧f; 277)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Hand</ets> + <ets>kerchief</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A piece of cloth, usually square and often fine and
elegant, carried for wiping the face or hands.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A piece of cloth shaped like a handkerchief to be
worn about the neck; a neckerchief; a neckcloth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Handle</ent>⟦br⟧
